28/05/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Officers of the State Protection and Investigation Agency arrested four Bosnian Serbs Tuesday (May 27th) on suspicion of torturing and murdering Bosnian Muslim and Croat prisoners in August 1992. Arrested in the Bosnian Serb town of Prijedor, they may have participated in the murders of more than 250 Bosnian Muslims and Croat prisoners at Koricanske Stijene in central Bosnia.
Separately, Federation of BiH police conducted a wide-scale operation Monday against a local child pornography ring. The interior ministry says police searched 22 properties and launched investigations against 48 people. (Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 28/05/08; Fena, RTRS, PBS, DPA - 27/05/08)
